 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">Wooly =
Mice!</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 2=
6px;font-size: 16px;">Colossal Biosciences has successfully inserted woolly=
 mammoth DNA into mice, creating &#8220;woolly mice&#8221; with shaggy fur =
and enhanced fat metabolism&#8212;traits that helped mammoths survive the I=
ce Age. In doing so, Colossal demonstrated its ability to reintroduce extin=
ct traits using CRISPR gene editing. With the gene editing processes now va=
lidated, the next step is to move from mice to elephants, which as you migh=
t imagine is a much more complex process. And if all goes well there, the p=
lan is to have a living wooly mammoth by 2028.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 2=
0px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><span>This b=
reakthrough makes </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/02c94e18-=
af92-4da0-9dc0-c8ec961bf8f1?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXe=
pKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: rgb(54,55,55);text-decoration=
: underline;">this news</a><span> from early January make a lot more sense.=
 At the time, Colossal raised $200M at a $10.2B valuation. Presumably inves=
tors had a bit more visibility on what was coming down the pipeline from th=
e company than the general public, who kind of sneered and jeered at the fu=
ndraising. </span></p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);l=
ine-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">A $10B Wooly Mammoth startup?! Lol. </p>=
<p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-=
size: 16px;">We got Wooly Mice baby! Who&#8217;s laughing now? </p><p style=
=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16=
px;"><strong>(5)</strong><span> </span><strong><a href=3D"https://substack.=
com/redirect/e149f9a5-30a8-4394-b67a-c4f6f584e1fa?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb=
8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: rgb(54,=
55,55);text-decoration: underline;">Aging activates escape of the silent X =
chromosome in the female mouse hippocampus</a></strong></p><p style=3D"marg=
in: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><em=
>Gadek et al in Science</em></p><blockquote style=3D"border-left: 4px solid=
 #0c2427;margin: 20px 0;padding: 0;"><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: =
rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><em>Sel=
ect genes on the Xi underwent activation, with new escape across cells incl=
uding in the dentate gyrus, critical to learning and memory. Expression of =
the Xi escapee Plp1, a myelin component, was increased in the aging hippoca=
mpus of female mice and parahippocampus of women. AAV-mediated Plp1 elevati=
on in the dentate gyrus of aging male and female mice improved cognition. U=
nderstanding how the Xi may confer female advantage could lead to novel tar=
gets that counter brain aging and disease in both sexes.</em></p></blockquo=
te><div class=3D"captioned-image-container-static" style=3D"font-size: 16px=
